# LeagueForge Permissions, Roles, Club Creation, and Database Schema
# Purpose: Define role-based access control, club creation workflow, role transitions, and database schema guidance.
# Intended use: Claude 4.6 / VS Code coding agent implementation reference.

app:
  name: LeagueForge
  tagline: Where competition is built and champions are forged.
  description: >
    A modern sports league management platform for clubs, coordinators, and players.
    The system supports club creation, league setup, player management, match scheduling,
    round robin generation, score validation, standings, and player statistics.

core_principles:
  - SiteAdmin permissions are global across the entire application.
  - ClubDirector permissions are scoped only to clubs they manage.
  - LeagueCoordinator permissions are scoped only to leagues they coordinate.
  - Player permissions are scoped to their own profile, personal stats, and league visibility.
  - ClubCreatorProvisional is a temporary role used while a submitted club is pending approval.
  - Club-scoped access should always be checked using club_id.
  - League-scoped access should always be checked using league_id and parent club_id.
  - Role changes should be auditable through role_events.

roles:
  - role_key: SiteAdmin
    display_name: Site Administrator
    scope: global
    description: >
      Highest privilege role. Can manage the full application, all clubs, all leagues,
      all players, global settings, analytics, and approval workflows.
    permissions:
      users:
        view_all: true
        edit_all: true
        suspend_all: true
        assign_roles: true
        remove_roles: true
      clubs:
        create: true
        view_all: true
        edit_all: true
        approve_pending: true
        reject_pending: true
        delete_all: true
        assign_club_director: true
        remove_club_director: true
      leagues:
        create_any: true
        view_all: true
        edit_all: true
        delete_all: true
      players:
        view_all: true
        edit_all: true
        suspend_all: true
      matches:
        view_all: true
        edit_all: true
        validate_all: true
        override_scores: true
      standings:
        view_all: true
        validate_all: true
        override_all: true
      analytics:
        view_site_reports: true
        view_all_club_reports: true
        export_site_data: true
      settings:
        site_config: true
        scoring_rules: true
        ranking_algorithm: true
        global_notifications: true

  - role_key: ClubDirector
    display_name: Club Director
    scope: club
    description: >
      Club-level administrator. Can manage leagues, coordinators, players, matches,
      schedules, scores, standings, and analytics only within assigned club boundaries.
    permissions:
      clubs:
        view_own: true
        edit_own: true
        manage_club_profile: true
        manage_club_logo: true
        delete_own: false
        approve_other_clubs: false
      club_admins:
        add_league_coordinator: true
        remove_league_coordinator: true
        assign_club_roles: true
      leagues:
        create_in_own_club: true
        view_own_club_leagues: true
        edit_own_club_leagues: true
        delete_own_club_leagues: true
      players:
        view_own_club_players: true
        add_players_to_club: true
        remove_players_from_club: true
        edit_player_status_in_club: true
        suspend_player_from_club: true
      matches:
        schedule_in_own_club: true
        view_own_club_matches: true
        edit_scores_in_own_club: true
        validate_results_in_own_club: true
      standings:
        view_own_club_standings: true
        validate_own_club_standings: true
        override_own_club_standings: true
      analytics:
        view_own_club_reports: true
        export_own_club_data: true
      settings:
        club_settings: true
        site_config: false
        global_notifications: false

  - role_key: LeagueCoordinator
    display_name: League Coordinator
    scope: league
    description: >
      Operational role for managing a specific league or play session. Can add/remove
      players before a session, generate round robins, update match results, and validate standings.
    permissions:
      clubs:
        view_parent_club: true
        edit_parent_club: false
      leagues:
        view_assigned_league: true
        edit_assigned_league: true
        create_league: false
        delete_league: false
      league_roster:
        view_league_players: true
        add_players_before_session: true
        remove_players_before_session: true
        edit_player_assignments: true
        lock_roster_for_session: true
      play_sessions:
        create_session: true
        edit_session: true
        open_check_in: true
        close_check_in: true
        generate_round_robin: true
        regenerate_round_robin_before_start: true
      matches:
        view_schedule: true
        generate_matches: true
        update_results: true
        correct_scores: true
        confirm_completed_matches: true
      standings:
        view_league_standings: true
        validate_league_standings: true
        verify_standings_after_session: true
      analytics:
        view_league_reports: true
        export_league_data: true
      settings:
        league_settings: true
        club_settings: false
        site_config: false

  - role_key: Player
    display_name: Player
    scope: self_and_joined_leagues
    description: >
      Standard account role. Can view league standings and match schedules for leagues
      they participate in, edit their own profile, and view advanced personal statistics.
    permissions:
      profile:
        view_self: true
        edit_self: true
        manage_own_login: true
      clubs:
        view_joined_clubs: true
        create_pending_club_submission: true
        edit_approved_club: false
      leagues:
        view_joined_leagues: true
        view_league_standings: true
        view_league_schedule: true
        request_to_join_league: true
      matches:
        view_own_matches: true
        view_league_results: true
        submit_score: false
        verify_own_score_when_enabled: true
        edit_score: false
      standings:
        view_joined_league_standings: true
        validate_standings: false
      analytics:
        view_personal_basic_stats: true
        view_personal_advanced_stats: true
        view_other_player_advanced_stats: false
        view_club_metrics: false
        export_data: false

  - role_key: ClubCreatorProvisional
    display_name: Club Creator Provisional
    scope: pending_club_submission
    description: >
      Temporary role assigned when a user submits a club for approval. The user can track
      submission status and edit the pending club submission, but cannot create leagues or
      manage players until approval.
    permissions:
      clubs:
        create_pending: true
        view_own_pending: true
        edit_pending: true
        track_approval_status: true
        withdraw_pending_submission: true
        view_all_pending: false
        approve_pending: false
        reject_pending: false
      leagues:
        create: false
        edit: false
        delete: false
      players:
        view_self_stats: true
        manage_club_players: false
      matches:
        view: false
        create: false
        edit: false
      standings:
        view: false
        validate: false
      analytics:
        view_personal_basic_stats: true
        view_club_reports: false
        export_data: false

role_hierarchy:
  highest_to_lowest:
    - SiteAdmin
    - ClubDirector
    - LeagueCoordinator
    - Player
  provisional_roles:
    - ClubCreatorProvisional
  transition_notes:
    - Player can submit a club creation request.
    - After club submission, user receives ClubCreatorProvisional scoped to that pending club.
    - If SiteAdmin approves the club, ClubCreatorProvisional transitions to ClubDirector for that club.
    - If SiteAdmin rejects the club, user remains Player and does not gain ClubDirector access.

club_creation_workflow:
  initial_state:
    actor_role: Player
    action: create_club_submission
    result:
      create_club_record:
        status: pending
        creator_user_id: current_user.id
      assign_role:
        role_key: ClubCreatorProvisional
        scope: club_id
        active: true
  required_club_fields:
    - club_name
    - location
    - description
    - logo_url_optional
  pending_capabilities:
    - Creator can view own pending club submission.
    - Creator can edit own pending club submission.
    - Creator can track approval status.
    - Creator cannot create leagues yet.
    - Creator cannot manage players yet.
    - Creator cannot schedule matches yet.

role_transition_events:
  - event_key: ClubApproved
    trigger:
      table: clubs
      condition: status changes from any non-approved value to approved
    actor_allowed:
      - SiteAdmin
    actions:
      - update_club_status:
          status: approved
      - update_user_role:
          user_id: clubs.creator_user_id
          club_id: clubs.club_id
          from_role: ClubCreatorProvisional
          to_role: ClubDirector
          active: true
      - insert_role_event:
          event_type: ClubApproved
          old_role: ClubCreatorProvisional
          new_role: ClubDirector
          notes: Club approval promoted user to ClubDirector.
      - notify_user:
          message: Your club has been approved. You now have Club Director permissions.

  - event_key: ClubRejected
    trigger:
      table: clubs
      condition: status changes from any non-rejected value to rejected
    actor_allowed:
      - SiteAdmin
    actions:
      - update_club_status:
          status: rejected
      - keep_user_role:
          user_id: clubs.creator_user_id
          effective_role: Player
          no_director_access: true
      - insert_role_event:
          event_type: ClubRejected
          old_role: ClubCreatorProvisional
          new_role: null
          notes: Club proposal rejected. User remains Player.
      - notify_user:
          message: Your club proposal was rejected. You remain a Player.

database_schema:
  tables:
    users:
      description: Stores authenticated application users.
      fields:
        user_id:
          type: uuid_or_string
          primary_key: true
          notes: Should align with Firebase Auth uid if using Firebase.
        username:
          type: string
          unique: true
          required: true
        email:
          type: string
          unique: true
          required: true
        password_hash:
          type: string
          required: false
          notes: Do not store password_hash if using Firebase Auth. Firebase owns credential storage.
        created_at:
          type: timestamp
        updated_at:
          type: timestamp

    roles:
      description: Defines allowed system roles.
      fields:
        role_id:
          type: string
          primary_key: true
          examples:
            - SiteAdmin
            - ClubDirector
            - LeagueCoordinator
            - Player
            - ClubCreatorProvisional
        role_name:
          type: string
          unique: true
          required: true
        description:
          type: string

    user_roles:
      description: Assigns users to roles with optional club and league scope.
      fields:
        user_role_id:
          type: uuid_or_string
          primary_key: true
        user_id:
          type: uuid_or_string
          foreign_key: users.user_id
          required: true
        role_id:
          type: string
          foreign_key: roles.role_id
          required: true
        club_id:
          type: uuid_or_string
          foreign_key: clubs.club_id
          nullable: true
          notes: Null for global roles like SiteAdmin. Required for ClubDirector and ClubCreatorProvisional.
        league_id:
          type: uuid_or_string
          foreign_key: leagues.league_id
          nullable: true
          notes: Required for LeagueCoordinator if coordinator assignment is league-specific.
        assigned_at:
          type: timestamp
        assigned_by:
          type: uuid_or_string
          nullable: true
          notes: User id of assigning admin when applicable.
        active:
          type: boolean
          default: true

    clubs:
      description: Stores club records and club approval status.
      fields:
        club_id:
          type: uuid_or_string
          primary_key: true
        club_name:
          type: string
          unique: true
          required: true
        location:
          type: string
          required: true
        description:
          type: string
          required: false
        logo_url:
          type: string
          required: false
        status:
          type: enum
          values:
            - pending
            - approved
            - rejected
          default: pending
        creator_user_id:
          type: uuid_or_string
          foreign_key: users.user_id
          required: true
        created_at:
          type: timestamp
        updated_at:
          type: timestamp

    leagues:
      description: Stores leagues under approved clubs.
      fields:
        league_id:
          type: uuid_or_string
          primary_key: true
        league_name:
          type: string
          required: true
        club_id:
          type: uuid_or_string
          foreign_key: clubs.club_id
          required: true
        season:
          type: string
          required: false
        start_date:
          type: date
          required: false
        end_date:
          type: date
          required: false
        created_at:
          type: timestamp
        updated_at:
          type: timestamp

    league_memberships:
      description: Connects players to leagues.
      fields:
        league_membership_id:
          type: uuid_or_string
          primary_key: true
        league_id:
          type: uuid_or_string
          foreign_key: leagues.league_id
          required: true
        user_id:
          type: uuid_or_string
          foreign_key: users.user_id
          required: true
        status:
          type: enum
          values:
            - active
            - inactive
            - waitlisted
            - removed
          default: active
        joined_at:
          type: timestamp

    play_sessions:
      description: Represents a scheduled play session for a league.
      fields:
        play_session_id:
          type: uuid_or_string
          primary_key: true
        league_id:
          type: uuid_or_string
          foreign_key: leagues.league_id
          required: true
        session_date:
          type: timestamp
          required: true
        status:
          type: enum
          values:
            - scheduled
            - check_in_open
            - in_progress
            - completed
            - validated
          default: scheduled
        created_by:
          type: uuid_or_string
          foreign_key: users.user_id
        created_at:
          type: timestamp
        updated_at:
          type: timestamp

    matches:
      description: Stores generated or scheduled matches.
      fields:
        match_id:
          type: uuid_or_string
          primary_key: true
        league_id:
          type: uuid_or_string
          foreign_key: leagues.league_id
          required: true
        play_session_id:
          type: uuid_or_string
          foreign_key: play_sessions.play_session_id
          nullable: true
        round_number:
          type: integer
          nullable: true
        player1_id:
          type: uuid_or_string
          foreign_key: users.user_id
          required: true
        player2_id:
          type: uuid_or_string
          foreign_key: users.user_id
          required: true
        scheduled_at:
          type: timestamp
          nullable: true
        score_player1:
          type: integer
          nullable: true
        score_player2:
          type: integer
          nullable: true
        status:
          type: enum
          values:
            - scheduled
            - in_progress
            - completed
            - validated
          default: scheduled
        created_at:
          type: timestamp
        updated_at:
          type: timestamp

    role_events:
      description: Audit table for role changes and approval events.
      fields:
        event_id:
          type: uuid_or_string
          primary_key: true
        user_id:
          type: uuid_or_string
          foreign_key: users.user_id
          required: true
        club_id:
          type: uuid_or_string
          foreign_key: clubs.club_id
          nullable: true
        league_id:
          type: uuid_or_string
          foreign_key: leagues.league_id
          nullable: true
        event_type:
          type: string
          examples:
            - ClubApproved
            - ClubRejected
            - RoleAssigned
            - RoleRemoved
        old_role_id:
          type: string
          foreign_key: roles.role_id
          nullable: true
        new_role_id:
          type: string
          foreign_key: roles.role_id
          nullable: true
        event_timestamp:
          type: timestamp
        notes:
          type: string

access_control_rules:
  site_admin:
    allow_when:
      - user has active user_roles record where role_id == SiteAdmin and club_id is null
  club_director:
    allow_when:
      - user has active user_roles record where role_id == ClubDirector and club_id matches target club_id
  league_coordinator:
    allow_when:
      - user has active user_roles record where role_id == LeagueCoordinator and league_id matches target league_id
      - or user has ClubDirector role for parent club_id of target league
      - or user has SiteAdmin role
  player:
    allow_when:
      - user is viewing own profile
      - user is viewing leagues where they have active league_memberships record
      - user is viewing standings or schedule for joined league
  club_creator_provisional:
    allow_when:
      - user has active user_roles record where role_id == ClubCreatorProvisional and club_id matches pending club_id
      - target club status == pending

implementation_notes_for_firebase:
  firestore_collections:
    - users
    - roles
    - userRoles
    - clubs
    - leagues
    - leagueMemberships
    - playSessions
    - matches
    - roleEvents
  recommended_document_ids:
    users: Firebase Auth uid
    roles: role_key such as SiteAdmin or ClubDirector
    clubs: auto-generated id
    leagues: auto-generated id
    userRoles: auto-generated id or composite userId_role_scope
  security_rules_guidance:
    - Never trust UI-only role checks.
    - Enforce role checks in Firestore Security Rules or backend Cloud Functions.
    - Use custom claims only for global roles if needed, such as SiteAdmin.
    - Use Firestore role documents for scoped roles because ClubDirector and LeagueCoordinator are resource-specific.
    - Validate that a ClubDirector club_id matches the requested club document.
    - Validate that a LeagueCoordinator league_id matches the requested league document.
    - Only SiteAdmin can approve or reject pending clubs.
    - A pending club creator can update only limited fields on their own pending club.
    - On club approval, use a trusted backend function to update userRoles and roleEvents atomically.

agent_tasks:
  - Create or update role constants for SiteAdmin, ClubDirector, LeagueCoordinator, Player, and ClubCreatorProvisional.
  - Create TypeScript types for RoleKey, ClubStatus, LeagueStatus, PlaySessionStatus, MatchStatus, and scoped UserRole.
  - Create Firestore collection helpers for users, roles, userRoles, clubs, leagues, leagueMemberships, playSessions, matches, and roleEvents.
  - Add permission helper functions:
      - isSiteAdmin(userId)
      - isClubDirector(userId, clubId)
      - isLeagueCoordinator(userId, leagueId)
      - canApproveClub(userId)
      - canEditPendingClub(userId, clubId)
      - canManageLeagueRoster(userId, leagueId)
      - canValidateStandings(userId, leagueId)
      - canViewPlayerAdvancedStats(requestingUserId, targetUserId)
  - Add club creation flow:
      - Player submits club.
      - Create clubs document with status pending.
      - Create userRoles document for ClubCreatorProvisional scoped to club_id.
      - Show status tracking UI.
      - Allow edits while status is pending.
  - Add site admin approval flow:
      - SiteAdmin reviews pending clubs.
      - SiteAdmin approves or rejects.
      - Backend function updates club status.
      - Backend function updates user role on approval.
      - Backend function writes roleEvents audit record.
      - Backend function creates user notification.
